OL,3,CWhy Hungary's election matters
OL,5,FFor his part, Magyar has promised to
OL,6,Fwork constructively with the European
OL,7,FUnion on Ukraine, take a firmer line
OL,8,Fwith Putin and revisit many of
OL,9,FHungary's existing energy arrangements
OL,10,Fwith Russia ` all of which could
OL,11,Fsignificantly bolster European unity
OL,12,Fwhen it comes to Ukraine.
OL,14,FBut the opposition leader is not
OL,15,Fwithout his critics. Pro-Fidesz
OL,16,Fbillboards across the country paint
OL,17,FUkrainian President Volodymyr
OL,18,FZelenskyy and EU chief Ursula von der
OL,19,FLeyen as fierce opponents of Hungary
OL,20,Fthat only Orban can defend against.
OL,26,@|D@Nrp
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
